Motion hearing on September 25, 2020 at 02:00 pm.

09:00 AM  Hearing is taking place via Zoom and live streamed on YouTube Live for public access purposes. Defendant Ann M Chapman appeared by phone means. Prosecuting Atty Scott E. Niemi appeared by video means through Zoom for State of Wisconsin.  Today is a continued motion hearing.  Court recaps previous hearing indicating hearing was adjourned for defendant to decide if she wanted counsel and if so, to obtain an attorney.  Defendant states that she contacted the Public Defender's Office and doesn't qualify due to her employment and her husband's income.  Continued by stating that she attempted to call private counsel, but has yet to receive a response.  Defendant's address verified on the record.  Clerk confirms that the $2,000 posted due to the previous active warrant, has been received and is currently being held.  Court will modify bond to $2,500 signature with same condtions.  The Court instructs the defendant that once the bond is received, it is to immediately be signed and returned to the court.  Once bond is returned, the $2,000 being held can be released to the DA Trust Account to be applied to restitution owed.  Bond form.  Motion hearing scheduled for September 25, 2020 at 02:00 pm.
Motion hearing on August 27, 2020 at 09:00 am.

11:52 AM  Hearing is taking place via Zoom and live streamed on YouTube Live for public access purposes.  Defendant Ann M Chapman appeared by phone means. Prosecuting Atty Scott E. Niemi appeared by video means through Zoom for State of Wisconsin.  Motion to Revoke Deferred Entry of Judgment filed 8/22/17 and on 9/18/17 the DEJ was extended to provide time to pay restitution.  Additional adjournments were made as noted by Judge.  ADA Niemi states that there is about $7,800 still due in restitution and $2,000 was posted when arrested on warrant for non-appearance at last scheduled hearing.  Court states that this case has really never went to a motion hearing, the defendant has a right to counsel, and would need to call the Public Defender's office to see if she would still qualify.  Defendant indicates that she just started a job and would be able to make bi-weekly payments towards the restitution.  ADA Niemi would still like to move forward with the motion hearing to revoke the DEJ.  Court will set the motion hearing for 8/27/2020 at 9 am.
